    $$\ddP{\emom[i]'}=\ddP{\emom[i]+q_i}=\dn[4]q_i\,\ndeltafn{(\emom[i]+q_i)^2-m_i^2} \thetafn{\emom^0_i+q_i^0}$$
            Now since we also have the on shell enforcing delta function from $\ddP{\emom[i]}$ we can rewrite the delta functions:     $$\ddP{\emom[i]}\,\ndeltafn{(\emom[i]+q_i)^2-m_i^2}=\ddP{\emom[i]}\ndeltafn{\underbracket{(\emom[i]^2-m_i^2)}_{\text{redundant}}+2 \emom[i] \cdot q_i+q_i^2}=\ddP{\emom[i]}\ndeltafn{2 \emom[i] \cdot q_i+q_i^2}$$
            Finally when integrating over $q_2$ we choose to hit $\ndeltafn[(4)]{\emom[1]+\emom[2]-\emom[1]'-\emom[2]'}=\ndeltafn[(4)]{q_1+q_2}$ and thus we just set $q_2=-q_1$

